Michigan Democratic Representative Rashida Tlaib was detained by police as she participated in a demonstration at Detroit Metropolitan Airport (DTW) Friday.
Tlaib joined with airport catering employees in their protest for higher wages and a better health care program.
"U.S. Rep. Rashida Tlaib eventually agreed to move; however, she chose to ride to the police department with the other demonstrators.
— Rashida Tlaib (@RashidaTlaib) February 14, 2020"We won't stop until we get #fairwages & #healthcare," Tlaib wrote.
